### Action Verbs

Use consistent verbs for common actions:

| Action | Verb | Example |
|--------|------|---------|
| Make new | Create | "Create an instance" |
| Remove | Delete | "Delete the instance" |
| Change | Update/Modify | "Update the password" |
| Start again | Resume | "Resume the instance" |
| Stop temporarily | Pause | "Pause the instance" |
| Make bigger/smaller | Resize | "Resize the instance" |
| Move up tier | Upgrade | "Upgrade to Professional" |

### Capitalization Rules

1. **Product names** - Always capitalize: Neo4j, Aura, Cypher
2. **Features** - Capitalize when referring to the tool: Query tool, Explore tool
3. **Generic terms** - Lowercase: instance, database, node, relationship
4. **UI elements** - Bold and match UI exactly: **Create Instance**

### Avoid These Terms

| Avoid | Use Instead |
|-------|-------------|
| Server | Instance |
| Cluster (for single instance) | Instance |
| DB | Database or Instance |
| Graph database (when meaning instance) | Instance |
| On-premises | Self-Managed |
| Enterprise Edition | Self-Managed Neo4j |

